The paper deals with the problem of leader election among mobile agents operating in a network modeled as an undirected graph. This problem falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) as it involves multiple agents operating in a distributed environment. The paper also deals with graph theory and algorithms for navigating the graph, which falls under the category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The problem of leader election also involves information sharing and communication among agents, which falls under the category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). The paper also deals with the movement of agents in the graph, which falls under the category of Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of anonymity, which falls under the category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI).
